The Netflix MTG series has some good talent involved:

"The Russos are set to executive produce the series, with writers Henry Gilroy (Star Wars Rebels, Star Wars: The Clone Wars) and Jose Molina (The Tick, Jordan Peele’s Weird City) serving as showrunners. Yoriaki Mochizuki (Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse) is on board as supervising director and co-executive producer."
What exactly does a show runner do?
I'm aware, but...for everyone else that may not know
There are some people who worked on Devilman Crybaby on it too
That makes me super hyped
devilman crybaby is weird, but good
100% wierd, But the animation and drama is top notch imo
Boo notch eh?
Where does that fall between top and bottom notches?
Show runners do exactly as the name indicates. They oversee the entire production, from hiring directors/writers, to production look/feel, to maintaining and guiding the story, etc.
So executive producer type stuffs?
closer to manager stuff

No - it's very different, actually. EP's can be a symbolic title and typically they're mostly involved with financing the production and dealing with things at a macro level, while show runners deal with the minutia.
Gotcha, so the anti-EP to an extent
In a way. Show runners are involved with the day to day and wear many hats.
Do you run for any shows?
No, but have friends who have.
I ran for the march of dimes once
I was tired after
I ran to breakfast once.
once.
Would you recommend it?
I slipped on a bagel and sprained my tongue, so probably not.
Noted. I shan't be running to breakfast or any food events moving forward on your recommendation
It's not uncommon for show runners to be writers as managing the story in a long-form format is critical.
Directors are sometimes the show runner equivalent on a movie, but not always
Yeah...it's funny, movies don't really have the same thing because you're typically telling a single story, but you could think of Kevin Feige as being the MCU's show runner

Quentin Tarrentino and Martin Scorsese are probably the closest. They're actually doing cinematography and directing performances and tweaking dialogue and probably even fucking with wardrobe choices and picking music, etc.
PTA probably would be in there too
I think they just call those guys control freaks...
:smiling_imp:
Sure, lol, but they're also those rare examples of people who aren't wrong when they think they can do every job better than anyone around them
well, usually not wrong
Behind every great director is an amazing director of cinematography.
I’m glad we could clear this up for everyone so they could know what I clearly already knew.
You're the best, <@U33EGB4TX>!
Clearly
Thank you, Matt :,)

If someone is playing a pub stompy deck, and they go off, you can offer them to borrow a deck more on your power level, and if they don’t want that, then go play with someone else.
